# Ownership is deliberately narrow rather than a blanket "* @anthony-liddle".
# These are the paths where an unreviewed change would do the most damage: the
# workflow that publishes to npm over OIDC, and the package metadata that
# decides what gets published and under what name. Everything else is covered
# by the ordinary review requirement on main.
#
# On a solo repo this is future-proofing. It costs nothing today and becomes
# load-bearing the moment a second person has merge rights.

.github/workflows/release.yml @anthony-liddle
package.json @anthony-liddle

# Owning this file too, so ownership cannot be quietly removed by a PR that
# edits it.
.github/CODEOWNERS @anthony-liddle
